#. <section class="sutta" id="mn146"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn146:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 146"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 146"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn146:0.2"
msgid "Nandakovādasutta"
msgstr "Advice from Nandaka"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn146:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn146:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn146:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mahāpajāpatigotamī pañcamattehi bhikkhunisatehi saddhiṃ yena "
"bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ "
"aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho mahāpajāpatigotamī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Mahāpajāpatī Gotamī together with around five hundred nuns approached "
"the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side, and said to him:"

msgctxt "mn146:2.2"
msgid "“ovadatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhuniyo;"
msgstr "“Sir, may the Buddha please advise"

msgctxt "mn146:2.3"
msgid "anusāsatu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhuniyo;"
msgstr "and instruct the nuns."

#. VAR: dhammiṃ kathan”ti → dhammikathanti (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn146:2.4"
msgid "karotu, bhante, bhagavā bhikkhunīnaṃ dhammiṃ kathan”ti."
msgstr "Please give the nuns a Dhamma talk.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn146:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadanti pariyāyena."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the senior mendicants were taking turns to advise the nuns."

msgctxt "mn146:3.2"
msgid "Āyasmā nandako na icchati bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ pariyāyena."
msgstr "But Venerable Nandaka didn’t want to take his turn."

msgctxt "mn146:3.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Ānanda:"

msgctxt "mn146:3.4"
msgid ""
"“kassa nu kho, ānanda, ajja pariyāyo bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ pariyāyenā”ti?"
msgstr "“Ānanda, whose turn is it to advise the nuns today?”"

#. VAR: Sabbeheva, bhante, kato → nandakassa bhante (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn146:3.5"
msgid "“Sabbeheva, bhante, kato pariyāyo bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ pariyāyena."
msgstr "“It’s Nandaka’s turn, sir,"

msgctxt "mn146:3.6"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ, bhante, āyasmā nandako na icchati bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ pariyāyenā”ti."
msgstr "but he doesn’t want to do it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.271"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn146:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ nandakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Nandaka:"

msgctxt "mn146:4.2"
msgid "“ovada, nandaka, bhikkhuniyo;"
msgstr "“Nandaka, please advise"

msgctxt "mn146:4.3"
msgid "anusāsa, nandaka, bhikkhuniyo;"
msgstr "and instruct the nuns."

msgctxt "mn146:4.4"
msgid "karohi tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhunīnaṃ dhammiṃ kathan”ti."
msgstr "Please, brahmin, give the nuns a Dhamma talk.”"

msgctxt "mn146:4.5"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā nandako bhagavato paṭissutvā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ "
"nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied Nandaka. Then, in the morning, he robed up and, taking "
"his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms."

# The Royal monastery is also full of nuns at SN 55.11.
msgctxt "mn146:4.6"
msgid ""
"Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto attadutiyo "
"yena rājakārāmo tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"He wandered for alms in Sāvatthī. After the meal, on his return from alms-"
"round, he went to the Royal Monastery with a companion."

msgctxt "mn146:4.7"
msgid "Addasaṃsu kho tā bhikkhuniyo āyasmantaṃ nandakaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr "Those nuns saw him coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "mn146:4.8"
msgid "Disvāna āsanaṃ paññāpesuṃ, udakañca pādānaṃ upaṭṭhapesuṃ."
msgstr "so they spread out a seat and placed water for washing the feet."

msgctxt "mn146:4.9"
msgid "Nisīdi kho āyasmā nandako paññatte āsane."
msgstr "Nandaka sat down on the seat spread out,"

msgctxt "mn146:4.10"
msgid "Nisajja pāde pakkhālesi."
msgstr "and washed his feet."

msgctxt "mn146:4.11"
msgid ""
"Tāpi kho bhikkhuniyo āyasmantaṃ nandakaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "Those nuns bowed, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "mn146:4.12"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho tā bhikkhuniyo āyasmā nandako etadavoca:"
msgstr "Nandaka said to them:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn146:5.1"
msgid "“paṭipucchakathā kho, bhaginiyo, bhavissati."
msgstr "“Sisters, this talk shall be in the form of questions."

msgctxt "mn146:5.2"
msgid ""
"Tattha ājānantīhi: ‘ājānāmā’ tissa vacanīyaṃ, na ājānantīhi: ‘na ājānāmā’ "
"tissa vacanīyaṃ."
msgstr "When you understand, say so. When you don’t understand, say so."

msgctxt "mn146:5.3"
msgid "Yassā vā panassa kaṅkhā vā vimati vā ahameva tattha paṭipucchitabbo:"
msgstr "If anyone has a doubt or uncertainty, ask me about it:"

msgctxt "mn146:5.4"
msgid "‘idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ; imassa kvattho’”ti?"
msgstr "‘Why, sir, does it say this? What does that mean?’”"

#. VAR: abhiraddhā → abhinandāma (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn146:5.5"
msgid ""
"“Ettakenapi mayaṃ, bhante, ayyassa nandakassa attamanā abhiraddhā yaṃ no "
"ayyo nandako pavāretī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“We’re already delighted and satisfied with Venerable Nandaka, since he "
"invites like this.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.272"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn146:6.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhaginiyo, "
msgstr "“What do you think, sisters? "

msgctxt "mn146:6.2"
msgid "cakkhu niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is the eye permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "mn146:6.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn146:6.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "mn146:6.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn146:6.6"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "mn146:6.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "mn146:6.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn146:6.9"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhaginiyo, "
msgstr "“What do you think, sisters? "

msgctxt "mn146:6.10"
msgid "sotaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is the ear …"

msgctxt "mn146:6.11"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn146:6.12"
msgid "ghānaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "nose …"

msgctxt "mn146:6.13"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” …"
msgstr ""

